## Case 6: HTTPS Port 443 Not Serving in Apache2

### Problem Statement
Port 443 listening di Ubuntu Server tetapi Apache2 tidak serve HTTPS. Browser redirect ke HTTP atau error.

### Investigation Steps
```bash
# Check port 443 status
sudo ss -tuln | grep 443
# Result: Port listen tapi HTTPS tidak jalan

# Check SSL module
sudo apache2ctl -M | grep ssl
# Result: mod_ssl not enabled

# Check certificate
ls -la /etc/ssl/certs/apache-selfsigned.crt
# Result: File not found
```

### Root Cause Analysis
1. SSL module (`mod_ssl`) tidak enabled
2. Self-signed certificate tidak ada di server
3. Default-SSL VirtualHost tidak enabled

### Solution Applied
```bash
# 1. Enable SSL module
sudo a2enmod ssl

# 2. Create self-signed certificate
sudo openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -keyout /etc/ssl/private/apache-selfsigned.key \
  -out /etc/ssl/certs/apache-selfsigned.crt

# 3. Enable default-ssl site
sudo a2ensite default-ssl

# 4. Restart Apache
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

### Verification
```bash
sudo ss -tuln | grep 443
# Output: LISTEN *:443 ✓

curl -k https://192.168.1.46
# Output: Apache2 Default Page ✓
```

### Key Learnings
- SSL module = required untuk HTTPS
- Certificate = mandatory untuk TLS handshake
- Self-signed cert OK untuk dev, butuh CA-signed untuk production
- Port listening ≠ service working → verify dengan test actual connection
